"title": "5476: property, nature of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5476",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Possessions are a gift from God to be used for his glory, for human pleasure and in benefiting others.</p>\n<h2>Possessions are a cause for thanksgiving</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:19\">ECC 5:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:2-Gen39:4\">GEN 39:2–39:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:18\">DEU 8:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:12\">1CH 29:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:21\">2CH 31:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:8\">HOS 2:8</a></p>\n<h2>Owning possessions is open to abuse</h2>\n<h3>They can be coveted</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:17\">EXO 20:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:1-1Kgs21:4\">1KI 21:1–21:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:13\">JER 6:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic2:2\">MIC 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:15\">LUK 12:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:29-1Cor7:31\">1CO 7:29–7:31</a></p>\n<h3>They can cause deceit</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:1-Acts5:9\">ACT 5:1–5:9</a></p>\n<h3>They can cause pride and forgetfulness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:9\">PRO 30:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs20:13-2Kgs20:17\">2KI 20:13–20:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:30\">DAN 4:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:20\">DAN 5:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos13:6\">HOS 13:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:24\">MAT 19:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:13-Luke12:21\">LUK 12:13–12:21</a></p>\n<h3>Abuse of ownership leads to judgment</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa3:16-Isa3:24\">ISA 3:16–3:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:8\">ISA 5:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:6-Hab2:9\">HAB 2:6–2:9</a></p>\n<h2>Property is for benefiting others</h2>\n<h3>It is to be used to help others</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:44-Acts2:45\">ACT 2:44–2:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:32-Acts4:35\">ACT 4:32–4:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:6\">GAL 6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:10\">GAL 6:10</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:28\">EPH 4:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:17-1Tim6:18\">1TI 6:17–6:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:15-Jas2:16\">JAS 2:15–2:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:17-1John3:18\">1JN 3:17–3:18</a></p>\n<h3>It is to be used to assist strangers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:35\">LEV 25:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num35:15\">NUM 35:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:19\">DEU 10:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:42\">MAT 5:42</a></p>\n<h2>Property provides no lasting satisfaction</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:26\">ECC 2:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job27:16-Job27:17\">JOB 27:16–27:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps39:6\">PSA 39:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:21\">ECC 2:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:4-Ezek28:7\">EZK 28:4–28:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hag1:6\">HAG 1:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:19-Matt6:21\">MAT 6:19–6:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:20-Luke12:21\">LUK 12:20–12:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:3\">JAS 5:3</a></p>\n<h2>Laws governing the inheritance of property</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:3-Num27:11\">NUM 27:3–27:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:15-Deut21:17\">DEU 21:15–21:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek46:16-Ezek46:18\">EZK 46:16–46:18</a></p>\n<h2>Godly men of property</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:2\">GEN 13:2</a> <em>Abraham</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:14\">GEN 26:14</a> <em>Isaac</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:43\">GEN 30:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:5\">GEN 32:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen36:7\">GEN 36:7</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:32\">2SA 19:32</a> <em>Barzillai</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:28\">1CH 29:28</a> <em>David</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr1:15\">2CH 1:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:22\">2CH 9:22</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr32:27-2Chr32:29\">2CH 32:27–32:29</a> <em>Hezekiah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job1:3\">JOB 1:3</a> <em>Job</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:57\">MAT 27:57</a> <em>Joseph of Arimathea</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:36-Acts4:37\">ACT 4:36–4:37</a> <em>Barnabas</em></p>",
